      { type: "p", text: "The Diagnostic Key:\nStatements 1, 3, 5, 7, and 9 are Planning. Why? Because they are entirely internal, controllable, and focused on operational efficiency or basic communication. They require no difficult choices and no sacrifices. You can do all of them simultaneously. They are the definition of an operational to-do list.\nStatements 2, 4, 6, 8, and 10 are Strategy. Why? Because they are external, risky, and focused on dominating a specific market with a specific advantage. Notice that Statement 6 explicitly dictates what the company will stop doing. Notice that Statement 8 designs a structural advantage (ERP integration) rather than a generic promise of \"good service.\"" },
      { type: "p", text: "Your Turn:\nOpen your company’s current \"Strategic Plan\" or the list of goals your team generated at your last offsite. Read through it honestly. Put a red pen through every single item that is an internal operational plan.\nWhat is left on the page?\nIf the page is entirely blank, your company is running completely blind into the market. You are relying purely on hard work to survive. It is time to stop planning, and start designing a way to win." }
